==English==
===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''git'''
#(''British slang'') A [[stupid]] or [[unpleasant]] person. As with most slang, the origins are old. A git is believed to be the [[illegitimate]] son of a [[prostitute]], putting an altogether more insulting spin on the term than is generally taken today. In common British parlance, being called a git would not be taken with great offence and freinds may use the term in, almost affectionate, fun-poking. Older generations or strangers may not be so forgiving or relaxed on being so-called.

